loogica / copycat  (http://loogica.net/)

copycat is a persistence tool which intercepts method calls, logging them 
into 'actions' to restore object state by re-executing these actions.

NOTES

If you are having problems you should check out common mistakes
<http://bitbucket.org/loogica/copycat/wiki/CommonMistakes> that happen when 
you first start working with this style of persistence.

How to use Clock <http://bitbucket.org/loogica/copycat/wiki/UsingClock>
to avoid date problems

DOCUMENTATION

Chec out pryvilege wiki http://bitbucket.org/loogica/copycat/wiki/Home

